text: Charles Allee (10 February 1848 - 7 June 1896) was an Australian cricketer. He played six first-class cricket matches for Victoria between 1873 and 1878. ==See also== * List of Victoria first-class cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1848 births Category:1896 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:Victoria cricketers Category:Cricketers from Melbourne
